=3D"1365" data-file-height=3D"1771"></a><figcaption>A group of actors as <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zombie" title=3D"Zombie">zombies</a>=
 during the shooting of the zombie apocalypse film <i>Meat Market 3</i></fi=
gcaption></figure>
<p><b>Zombie apocalypse</b> is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S=
ubgenre" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Subgenre">subgenre</a> of <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apocalyptic_and_post-apocalyptic_fiction"=
 title=3D"Apocalyptic and post-apocalyptic fiction">apocalyptic and post-ap=
ocalyptic fiction</a> in which <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soc=
ietal_collapse" title=3D"Societal collapse">society collapses</a> due to ov=
erwhelming swarms of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zombie" title=
=3D"Zombie">zombies</a>. Usually, only a few individuals or small bands of =
human survivors are left living.=20
</p><p>There are many different causes of a zombie apocalypse in fiction. I=
n some versions, the reason the dead rise and attack humans is unknown; in =
others, a parasite or infection is the cause - framing the film like a plag=
ue. Some stories have every corpse zombify regardless of the cause of death=
, whereas others require exposure to the infection, most commonly in the fo=
rm of a bite.
</p>
